    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-11-19T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-11-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="1526"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1526">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.41/300.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of the Navy</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 19, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inclose herewith a copy of a
                    memorandum from the British Ambassador at this capital, dated November 17, 1914,
                    requesting that, in view of a possible attack upon Tampico, the Senior Naval
                    Officer of the United States in Mexican waters be instructed to give such
                    protection as may be possible to the lives and interests of British subjects,
                    and to afford them refuge in the event of danger.</p>
                <p>I have the honor to suggest therefore that the Admiral in command in Mexican east
                    coast waters be instructed to extend such protection as may be possible to the
                    lives and properties of Americans, British, and other foreigners at Tampico, and
                    to afford them refuge in the event of danger.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
